Test::Count

Test::Count is a module to count and update the number of tests in
Test::More/etc.-based scripts. It supports a mini language for arithmetical
expressions in order to calculate the number of tests.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Test::Count

You can also look for information at:

    MetaCPAN
        http://metacpan.org/release/Test-Count

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Test::Count

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Test::Count

